# UI consistency

- **Surfaces and text:** Prefer `bg-surface-*`, `text-fg`, `text-fg-muted`, `accent-*`. Do not introduce `bg-navy-*`, `text-navy-*`, `border-navy-*`, or arbitrary `bg-[#...]` in `src/` (see `npm run ui:lint`).
- **Tokens:** Semantic colors and motion live in `src/styles/tokens.css`. Legacy `--bg-main` / `--text-main` are aliases only; new code should use semantic Tailwind classes.
- **Theme:** `applyTheme` sets `light` / `dark` on `<html>`. `applyUiDensity` sets `data-density` (`comfortable` | `compact`). Persist via `useSettingsStore` — do not toggle classes ad hoc in feature code.
- **Primitives:** Reuse `src/components/ui/*` (Button, Input, Select, Modal, PageHeader, Toolbar, …) before adding one-off styled elements.
- **Focus:** Use the `focus-ring` utility on custom interactive elements where appropriate; keep keyboard focus visible.
- **Docs:** `docs/design-system-reference.md` is the engineering reference; `docs/master-design-ui.md` remains the product/layout master.
